aa(lp11
VI'm going to start with how I started with this concept seven years ago,
p12
aVwhen Princess Diana died.
p13
aVThere was a sort of a standstill in Britain
p14
aVthe moment of her death,
p15
aVand people decided to mourn her death in a sort of mass way.
p16
aVI was fascinated by this phenomenon,
p17
aVso I wondered:
p18
aVcould one erase the image of Diana, actually quite crudely and physically?
p19
aVSo, I got a gun and started to shoot at the image of Diana,
p20
aVbut I couldn't erase this from my memory
p21
aVand certainly it was not being erased from the public psyche.
p22
aVMomentum was being built.
p23
aVThe press wrote about her death in rather, I felt, pornographic ways \u2014
p24
aVlike, "Which bit of artery left which bit of body?"
p25
aVand "How did she die in the back of the car?" \u2014
p26
aVand I was intrigued by this sort of mass voyeurism,
p27
aVso I made these rather gory images.
p28
aa(lp29
VI then went on wondering whether I could actually replace her image,
p30
aVso I got a look-alike of Diana
p31
aVand posed her in the right positions and angles
p32
aVand created something that was in, or existed in, the public imagination.
p33
aVSo people were wondering: was she going to marry Dodi?
p34
aVWas she in love with him?
p35
aVWas she pregnant? Did she want his baby?
p36
aVWas she pregnant when she died?
p37
aVSo I created this image of Diana, Dodi and their imaginary mixed-race child
p38
aVand this image came out, which caused a huge public outcry at the time.
p39
